    "confidence": "experimental",
    "notes": "WO-0073 production-scale candidate graph. Zone topology deliberately keeps each parent's new-child fan-out at or below its free-side count. _place_zones hardcodes the entry zone flush against the map's south edge (start = Rect(..., height - entry_height, ...)), so the entry zone (arrival_domestic) only has 3 usable sides (N/E/W), not 4 -- discovered while smoke-testing this graph, and distinct from WO-0071-IMPLEMENTATION-NOTES.md's star-topology finding (which covers small-parent/large-child spillover). route_south was folded into arrival_domestic's own beats rather than kept as a fourth child for exactly this reason -- it also matches production Map001's real geography, where the south route mouth (18,31) and Dock Messenger (21,28) sit immediately next to Elara's door (17,27). Every other zone keeps its new-child fan-out at or below its own 3 free sides (parent occupies the 4th). Beat names use the assembler's existing transfer/service/event/treasure keyword classification (assembler.py _build_map_plan); each beat's real EVT-HOM-*/TRN-HOM-* registry correspondence is recorded separately in the WO-0073 event-reconciliation table, not encoded in the beat string itself."
